The paper proposes a new algorithm for LiDAR odometry, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The algorithm uses surface normals and a unit sphere to estimate rotation, which involves computer vision techniques (cs.CV). The paper also mentions using a line cloud approach for translation estimation, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates its results on the KITTI dataset, which is commonly used in computer vision research (cs.CL).
